race.comment: CHARTIN (8) is racing well without winning, beaten narrowly in his last two. Was well supported last time when beaten a head, and only needs to hold his form over a favoured trip to go very close again. SHADOW HAWK (10) has a moderate winning strike-rate but performed well last time at this track, finishing second. Further improved third-up and should blend into the race beautifully from his draw. Gets his chance to break a long run of outs.. HARLEY'N'ROSE (2) tackled city class latest when fifth at Oakbank. Meets easier opposition this time. Has claims on his best form. SHARMA PRINCESS (6) improved sharply last time out to score by a nose at Penola two-and-a-half weeks ago. Drawn sticking but is worth following up. WARRANDYTE ROAD (4) has rediscovered his best form and only needs to hold that here to be competitive again.
